        "id": "docling_exam_paper_en-file-putnam-archive_2008_Solutions_2008s_page_005_21",
        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "First solution: (by Jacob Tsimerman) Note that any permutation is k-limited if and only if its inverse is klimited. Consequently, the number of k-limited permutations of {1,...,n} is the same as the number of k-limited involutions (permutations equal to their inverses) of {1,...,n}.",
        "bbox": [
          0.5582706724210608,
          0.4171511631470712,
          0.9210526329047538,
          0.5029761906258735
        ],
        "order": 13
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "eu_id": "EU-0009",
    "kind": "text_cluster_panel",
