        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "We use the following fact several times: the number of involutions of {1,...,n} is odd if n = 0, 1 and even otherwise. This follows from the fact that non-involutions come in pairs, so the number of involutions has the same parity as the number of permutations, namely n!.",
