        "observed_type": "text",
        "canon_role": "support_paragraph",
        "text": "Remark: More generally, the same proof shows that for any integers d, e > 1, h permutes the residue classes modulo p' if and only if it permutes the residue classes modulo pe. The argument used in the proof is related to a general result in number theory known as Hensel's lemma.",
